        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName><hi rend="italic">Down.</hi> | Beckenham | <hi rend="italic">Kent. S.E.</hi></placeName>
                    <date>Nov 29—1870</date>
                    <salute>Dear Sir</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                    <p>I have been informed that an application is to be made to Government for a pension for Mr Cupples.<ref target="#foot.f2"/></p>
                    <p>Although I am not personally acquainted with this gentleman, I have corresponded with him on scientific subject during several years.<ref target="#foot.f3"/></p>
                    <p>On some very intricate points he has been so kind as not only to collect, at the cost of much trouble, information from various sources, but has likewise made for me valuable observations. Therefore he has my sincere good wishes for his success. I have confined myself to the above points relating to Science, as I consider Literature beyond my province—</p>
                    <p>I beg leave to remain | dear Sir | yours faithfully | Charles Darwin</p>
                    
                </div>
            </div>
            

          
            
            
            
            
            
            
            
        </div>

        

        

